\cf2 \cb3 How do the rates of seafloor spreading for the Atlantic Ocean compare with those in the Pacific Ocean? What factors may affect these rates of spreading at mid-ocean ridges, notably whether the crust is being conserved or subducted at sites of convergence?\
\
4.)\
The rates of seafloor spreading are significantly lower in the Atlantic Ocean than the rates within the Pacific Ocean. This possibly could be caused subduction of the Pacific plate on the West boarder, while the plates within the Atlantic are converging into one another. Another cause could be the fact that the Pacific plate is made up of almost all ocean crust, while the plates comprising the Atlantic ocean contain large continental regions, bordering the Atlantic ocean almost completely.\
